1
00:00:05,667 --> 00:00:08,363
<i>Press down hard on the gas</i>

2
00:00:08,436 --> 00:00:12,304
<i>That's right, there's no compromise</i>

3
00:00:12,373 --> 00:00:16,366
<i>We'll slip through the night</i>

4
00:00:16,711 --> 00:00:19,202
<i>At the final moment push hard</i>

5
00:00:19,280 --> 00:00:23,341
<i>That's right, all the way to zero,</i>

6
00:00:23,418 --> 00:00:27,377
<i>Until we wipe away the days</i>

7
00:00:28,856 --> 00:00:33,589
<i>Gently open your heart</i>

8
00:00:34,295 --> 00:00:37,264
<i>If you pull it close to you</i>

9
00:00:39,701 --> 00:00:41,794
<i>It will reach you, without a doubt</i>

10
00:00:42,537 --> 00:00:43,834
<i>It will come, closer</i>

11
00:00:44,172 --> 00:00:46,732
<i>Now</i>

12
00:00:54,782 --> 00:01:00,152
<i>We're speeding through life,</i>
<i>squeezing it for all of its worth</i>

13
00:01:00,355 --> 00:01:01,515
<i>Our feet are tied</i>

14
00:01:01,589 --> 00:01:05,389
<i>But we still keep going farther</i>

15
00:01:05,727 --> 00:01:10,926
<i>Even if I take it back, and grasp it</i>

16
00:01:11,199 --> 00:01:12,530
<i>If you're not the one</i>

17
00:01:12,600 --> 00:01:13,999
<i>There will be no meaning</i>

18
00:01:14,068 --> 00:01:20,337
<i>And so we'll go far off into the distance.</i>

19
00:01:39,866 --> 00:01:40,890
Curse Sealing!

20
00:02:00,253 --> 00:02:01,481
Out of character.

21
00:02:01,554 --> 00:02:03,112
It appears he's quite tired...

22
00:02:03,890 --> 00:02:07,053
To think you've become able to
handle Sealing Jutsu...

23
00:02:09,395 --> 00:02:11,955
You've grown, eh, Kakashi?

24
00:02:17,403 --> 00:02:17,994
You...

25
00:02:26,245 --> 00:02:29,442
Long time no see, Kakashi.

26
00:02:31,684 --> 00:02:32,480
Orochimaru...

27
00:02:33,419 --> 00:02:39,551
Kakashi vs. Orochimaru:
Face to Face!

28
00:02:41,761 --> 00:02:42,887
Sorry, but...

29
00:02:44,263 --> 00:02:46,197
I have no business with you, Kakashi.

30
00:02:47,466 --> 00:02:49,491
But I do with the kid behind you.

31
00:02:55,374 --> 00:02:57,433
Why are you after Sasuke?!

32
00:02:59,612 --> 00:03:04,049
It's good for you.
You already got it, right?

33
00:03:06,285 --> 00:03:08,719
You didn't have it before, did you?

34
00:03:09,488 --> 00:03:10,079
That.

35
00:03:12,291 --> 00:03:13,223
That...

36
00:03:14,460 --> 00:03:16,189
left eye Sharingan!

37
00:03:20,533 --> 00:03:22,433
I want it, too...

38
00:03:24,704 --> 00:03:26,296
The Uchiha power.

39
00:03:40,653 --> 00:03:42,746
Come on. Get up.

40
00:03:53,032 --> 00:03:55,057
W-What?!

41
00:04:19,792 --> 00:04:21,089
<i>B-Bugs?</i>

42
00:04:21,827 --> 00:04:24,887
<i>They burst through the skin...</i>
<i>from inside his body?!</i>

43
00:04:25,998 --> 00:04:27,829
<i>What a creepy guy!</i>

44
00:04:30,503 --> 00:04:33,666
Heh! What kind of bluff
are you trying to pull?

45
00:04:51,157 --> 00:04:53,148
These things are called Parasitic Insects.

46
00:04:53,426 --> 00:04:56,452
They attack their pray in groups
and eat Chakra...

47
00:04:57,563 --> 00:04:59,428
If attacking in this amount...

48
00:05:00,032 --> 00:05:02,432
you're finished, no mistake.

49
00:05:05,071 --> 00:05:06,595
If you don't like that, give up.

50
00:05:07,273 --> 00:05:08,331
That would be in your best interests.

51
00:05:09,442 --> 00:05:11,740
If you use your left arm
technique on me,

52
00:05:12,611 --> 00:05:15,603
I'll simultaneously have the bugs exploit
the opening from behind.

53
00:05:16,816 --> 00:05:18,875
Conversely, if you use
your technique on the bugs,

54
00:05:19,652 --> 00:05:21,643
I'll simultaneously exploit the opening...

55
00:05:24,190 --> 00:05:27,819
Either way, you won't be able
to get through this.

56
00:05:30,663 --> 00:05:32,995
An ace in the hole is something
you set aside.

57
00:05:39,939 --> 00:05:42,407
Hey! Hold it!

58
00:05:47,780 --> 00:05:49,645
You little thief!

59
00:05:51,884 --> 00:05:53,875
Someone! Grab him!

60
00:06:02,161 --> 00:06:02,855
Uh oh.

61
00:06:31,390 --> 00:06:33,881
Man, what a pigheaded kid.

62
00:06:34,660 --> 00:06:36,525
Making us go to trouble!

63
00:07:36,455 --> 00:07:39,356
You have potential, boy.

64
00:08:01,113 --> 00:08:04,776
I liked your eyes earlier...

65
00:08:08,921 --> 00:08:13,153
If you come with me,
you can become strong.

66
00:08:16,562 --> 00:08:17,586
Follow me.

67
00:08:26,138 --> 00:08:30,268
<i>If you come with me,</i>
<i>you can become strong.</i>

68
00:08:35,914 --> 00:08:37,677
<i>You can become strong.</i>

69
00:08:52,264 --> 00:08:56,667
<i>Fight for me. If you do that...</i>

70
00:08:57,102 --> 00:08:59,127
<i>I'll make you stronger.</i>

71
00:10:00,933 --> 00:10:03,697
<i>Now, please live up to my expectations...</i>

72
00:10:12,111 --> 00:10:13,271
<i>No longer...</i>

73
00:10:16,115 --> 00:10:17,707
<i>will I...</i>

74
00:10:23,322 --> 00:10:26,553
<i>It seems like you're proud</i>
<i>of your arms. You!</i>

75
00:10:28,527 --> 00:10:29,357
<i>S-Stop it!</i>

76
00:10:33,198 --> 00:10:34,722
<i>Stop!</i>

77
00:10:40,572 --> 00:10:41,664
<i>No longer...</i>

78
00:10:45,010 --> 00:10:47,035
<i>can I make things</i>
<i>blow up in my face!</i>

79
00:10:54,052 --> 00:10:57,112
Don't... underestimate me!

80
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:19,040
An ace in the hole is something
you set aside, right?!

81
00:11:32,245 --> 00:11:36,011
An ace in the hole is something
you set aside, right?

82
00:11:39,752 --> 00:11:42,152
What?! He could already
use his right arm?!

83
00:11:44,924 --> 00:11:47,154
<i>So the first half of the battle was</i>
<i>a strategic move</i>

84
00:11:47,227 --> 00:11:49,923
<i>to make us think he couldn't</i>
<i>use his right arm.</i>

85
00:11:50,797 --> 00:11:52,788
<i>Not bad... Zaku.</i>

86
00:12:00,940 --> 00:12:01,998
What's your purpose?

87
00:12:03,109 --> 00:12:08,945
The recently built Sound Village.
That's my village, you see...

88
00:12:11,517 --> 00:12:14,247
You already understand, don't you?

89
00:12:14,921 --> 00:12:17,515
Humph! Ridiculous ambition.

90
00:12:18,358 --> 00:12:21,020
Oh, my... you said it.

91
00:12:22,328 --> 00:12:29,461
But, for that I need various pieces
who will obey my every whim.

92
00:12:31,337 --> 00:12:32,770
Take this!

93
00:12:34,641 --> 00:12:36,905
So Sasuke is one of those pieces?

94
00:12:37,410 --> 00:12:41,346
No. Sasuke is an exceptional piece.

95
00:12:42,181 --> 00:12:45,844
And the ones who are taking
the exams now...

96
00:12:48,788 --> 00:12:50,380
are mere throw away pieces.

97
00:13:05,939 --> 00:13:06,769
My arms!

98
00:13:15,949 --> 00:13:16,916
What's this?!

99
00:13:18,918 --> 00:13:21,409
Earlier when I recommended
that you give up...

100
00:13:21,988 --> 00:13:24,957
as a precautionary measure,
I gave a suggestion to the bugs...

101
00:13:26,526 --> 00:13:32,624
to block that troublesome wind hole
with their bodies and remain still.

102
00:13:33,900 --> 00:13:36,562
This is what a real ace in the hole is.

103
00:13:41,674 --> 00:13:42,663
Punk!

104
00:14:16,809 --> 00:14:19,471
Don't... come any closer... to Sasuke!

105
00:14:26,786 --> 00:14:30,347
Even if you're one of
the legendary three Ninja,

106
00:14:31,024 --> 00:14:34,187
at the least,
I can kill you as you kill me!

107
00:14:46,806 --> 00:14:48,000
What's funny?

108
00:14:50,043 --> 00:14:53,740
What you say and what you do,
are all off.

109
00:14:54,180 --> 00:14:54,976
What?

110
00:14:55,615 --> 00:14:59,244
There's no point at all in
attempting such a seal.

111
00:15:00,853 --> 00:15:02,013
You understand, don't you?

112
00:15:03,256 --> 00:15:05,087
The heart to seek out
in pursuit of the goal,

113
00:15:05,158 --> 00:15:08,855
no matter what obstructive power
there may be...

114
00:15:09,695 --> 00:15:12,095
He is the possessor of that quality.

115
00:15:13,299 --> 00:15:15,324
He's an avenger...

116
00:15:16,202 --> 00:15:17,863
So you took advantage of that, eh?

117
00:15:18,638 --> 00:15:19,764
However, Sasuke is...

118
00:15:20,406 --> 00:15:24,672
At some point,
he will definitely seek me out...

119
00:15:26,479 --> 00:15:28,310
in search of power.

120
00:15:30,917 --> 00:15:34,478
Oh, and, you're going to kill me?

121
00:15:35,254 --> 00:15:36,687
Why don't you try?

122
00:15:37,623 --> 00:15:39,250
That is, if you can...

123
00:15:55,408 --> 00:15:56,807
<i>Kill you as you kill me?!</i>

124
00:15:57,643 --> 00:15:59,042
<i>Am I an idiot?</i>

125
00:16:15,962 --> 00:16:18,522
It seems... it's over.

126
00:16:20,466 --> 00:16:22,559
The winner! Shino Aburame!

127
00:16:30,309 --> 00:16:34,177
W-What is he, Neji?!

128
00:16:38,885 --> 00:16:39,510
Byakugan!

129
00:16:45,358 --> 00:16:46,484
He's something else!

130
00:16:47,026 --> 00:16:50,052
I can understand him calling bugs
with a Summoning Jutsu...

131
00:16:50,796 --> 00:16:53,321
but he harbors bugs all over his body.

132
00:16:54,400 --> 00:16:55,833
S-Say what?!

133
00:16:56,736 --> 00:17:00,832
He's of the bug tamer race that
is passed down in the Leaf Village.

134
00:17:01,140 --> 00:17:03,165
Speaking of which,
I've heard of it...

135
00:17:03,976 --> 00:17:06,308
The story of a race that as
they come into this world,

136
00:17:06,612 --> 00:17:09,376
possess the secret technique of loaning
their bodies to bugs

137
00:17:09,916 --> 00:17:14,683
as a nest and fight using these bugs.

138
00:17:16,956 --> 00:17:21,484
They fully control the bugs and
entrust most of the battle to the bugs...

139
00:17:21,928 --> 00:17:24,988
I hear that they contract to keep
giving the bugs their own Chakra

140
00:17:25,064 --> 00:17:27,589
as food for compensation.

141
00:17:36,042 --> 00:17:39,500
So he's... the successor?

142
00:17:43,282 --> 00:17:45,273
That was unfortunate, Zaku.

143
00:17:45,851 --> 00:17:48,684
Why'd that happen to Zaku's arms?

144
00:17:49,956 --> 00:17:52,618
Probably, that guy called
Shino or whatever...

145
00:17:52,692 --> 00:17:55,820
exploited the opening and
stuck those bugs

146
00:17:55,928 --> 00:17:58,795
into the exhaust opening in Zaku's hands.

147
00:18:00,132 --> 00:18:02,657
If he were to fire the Slicing Sonic Wave
in that condition,

148
00:18:03,069 --> 00:18:08,132
the energy with no way out
would expand in search of an exit...

149
00:18:10,776 --> 00:18:13,108
His arms that are
gun barrels blow up...

150
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:16,448
and become useless.

151
00:18:24,490 --> 00:18:29,086
<i>Our relationship was only that</i>
<i>of having been given the same mission...</i>

152
00:18:30,096 --> 00:18:34,590
<i>but... l'll even the score for you.</i>

153
00:18:37,803 --> 00:18:41,398
<i>Whew. He gives me a chill, indeed...</i>

154
00:18:41,707 --> 00:18:42,867
What?! What?!

155
00:18:42,942 --> 00:18:47,504
So Shino, you were that strong,
weren't you?! Dang it!

156
00:18:47,880 --> 00:18:51,043
I thought he was
a creepy person from long before, but...

157
00:18:52,652 --> 00:18:53,311
Oh...

158
00:18:57,390 --> 00:18:59,984
S-Shino, good... work...

159
00:19:00,393 --> 00:19:01,860
Hey, you did it!

160
00:19:02,194 --> 00:19:05,061
Yes... I'm counting on you guys, too.

161
00:19:09,468 --> 00:19:13,404
<i>He comes back like he's</i>
<i>the team leader or something! Dang it!</i>

162
00:19:15,675 --> 00:19:20,237
Umm, now then, I would like to
get right to the next match.

163
00:19:24,650 --> 00:19:25,708
Kakashi Sensei!

164
00:19:26,719 --> 00:19:27,344
Yo!

165
00:19:27,720 --> 00:19:29,915
Not, "Yo! Kakashi Sensei!"

166
00:19:30,389 --> 00:19:33,324
What about Sasuke? Is he okay?

167
00:19:33,526 --> 00:19:35,016
Well, he's fine.

168
00:19:35,294 --> 00:19:36,989
He's sleeping soundly in the infirmary.

169
00:19:39,665 --> 00:19:42,532
<i>However, with Anbu Ops</i>
<i>standing as guards...</i>

170
00:19:43,002 --> 00:19:43,491
Oh.

171
00:19:43,636 --> 00:19:46,537
Tsurugi Misumi vs. Kankuro

172
00:19:48,007 --> 00:19:50,635
<i>It's finally my turn.</i>

173
00:19:50,910 --> 00:19:54,869
<i>Kankuro, he's totally underestimating this...</i>

174
00:19:55,381 --> 00:19:57,246
<i>Humph. Idiot...</i>

175
00:20:14,567 --> 00:20:15,465
<i>It's him!</i>

176
00:20:25,277 --> 00:20:29,145
Unlike Yoroi, I don't get
careless with kids at all.

177
00:20:31,951 --> 00:20:36,149
I'll say this first, once I do my technique...

178
00:20:36,956 --> 00:20:38,651
give up no matter what...

179
00:20:40,259 --> 00:20:41,658
I'll bring it to an end swiftly.

180
00:20:42,461 --> 00:20:43,655
If so, I'll also...

181
00:20:47,233 --> 00:20:49,463
bring it to an end swiftly!

182
00:20:55,808 --> 00:20:57,742
Now then, please begin...

183
00:20:58,711 --> 00:20:59,871
the third battle!

184
00:21:05,770 --> 00:21:10,400
<i>Hey, can you hear it?</i>

185
00:21:10,475 --> 00:21:18,712
<i>The clear, blue sky goes on and on</i>

186
00:21:19,651 --> 00:21:28,320
<i>The ocean spans limitlessly</i>

187
00:21:28,760 --> 00:21:36,633
<i>Please keep that smile on your face forever</i>

188
00:21:37,902 --> 00:21:43,568
<i>Or else I'll cry</i>

189
00:21:43,641 --> 00:21:47,407
<i>You won't have to search around you</i>

190
00:21:47,479 --> 00:21:51,040
<i>It's all ok now.</i>

191
00:21:51,382 --> 00:21:59,915
<i>Everyone is inside</i>
<i>this hand</i>

192
00:22:00,191 --> 00:22:05,390
<i>when you want to cry,</i>
<i>and you want to run away</i>

193
00:22:05,463 --> 00:22:09,866
<i>When you forget what happiness is</i>

194
00:22:09,934 --> 00:22:13,700
<i>Just sing.</i>

195
00:22:13,938 --> 00:22:19,103
<i>Light is born, and darkness was born</i>

196
00:22:19,177 --> 00:22:21,372
<i>The two are one</i>

197
00:22:21,479 --> 00:22:27,748
<i>Harmonia, feel the telepathy</i>

198
00:22:28,153 --> 00:22:33,352
<i>Hey, can you hear it?</i>

199
00:22:38,068 --> 00:22:41,037
I believed in your words the whole time.

200
00:22:41,738 --> 00:22:43,069
I wanted to be like you.

201
00:22:43,440 --> 00:22:45,305
I thought it would be nice
if that happened.

202
00:22:45,976 --> 00:22:48,911
So Ino, I want to fight the full tilt you.

203
00:22:49,146 --> 00:22:51,774
I'm no longer like I was before.

204
00:22:52,382 --> 00:22:56,011
There's no point if I don't
exceed the serious you.

205
00:22:57,187 --> 00:23:01,021
Next episode: "Kunoichi Rumble:
The Rivals Get Serious!"

206
00:23:01,558 --> 00:23:03,458
Let's have a fair fight.
